  ('en', 'wait', 'This is your official reminder: staring at the counter does not cook the burger faster.', 23),
  ('en', 'burger', 'Home of Indian Burgers means the bun showed up, but the masala took over the meeting.', 24),
  ('en', 'dad', 'Why did the tomato blush? Because it saw the salad dressing.', 25),
  ('en', 'food', 'Fries are just potatoes that finally found their purpose.', 26),
  ('en', 'wait', 'The food is not late. Your hunger is just being dramatic.', 27),
  ('en', 'dad', 'I asked the bun for advice. It said, stay grounded, but rise when needed.', 28),
  ('en', 'desi', 'Desi homes do not have snacks. They have emergency happiness stored in steel boxes.', 29),
  ('en', 'food', 'Sauce is proof that food can have a personality.', 30),
  ('en', 'wait', 'Waiting for food builds character. Mostly hungry character.', 31),
  ('en', 'dad', 'Why did the plate apply for a job? It wanted to serve.', 32),
  ('en', 'food', 'Crunch is just food applause.', 33),
